cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.HC 

The paper uses machine learning and computer vision techniques to analyze MR images of patients with mild traumatic brain injury. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves feature selection and classification, which are common topics in sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses bag-of-visual-words, which is a technique commonly used in image classification tasks, and could also be relevant to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
